<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Reid Hospitalized after Retaining WBC Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Robin Reid remained
hospitalized Friday after collapsing from exhaustion following his
WBC super-middleweight title defense.
</P>
<P>
Reid, who won a 12-round split decision Thursday night over
French challenger Hassine Cherifi, was lying at Whiston Hospital.
</P>
<P>
The British boxer spoke in a television interview after the
fight, but collapsed in his dressing room a few minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Reid, who never lost consciousness, had been expected to be
released from Whiston Hospital on Friday morning. But doctors said
he was being kept Friday afternoon for more observation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
