<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Intl Water Conference Begins Monday in Harare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 12 (Xinhua) -- About 200 delegates from all
over the world are expected in Harare next week to attend the
second Southern Africa Water and Waste Water Conference which
seeks solutions to water problems.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the five-day meeting which opens Monday is:
''Water security: guarding resources against drought and
pollution''. The conference will be held in conjunction with the
Water Africa '97 Exhibition.
</P>
<P>
The delegates include engineers, managers, scientists and
academics as well as wastewater professionals from Zimbabwe and
other southern African countries, and they will exchange
experiences and seek solutions to the escalating problems of
water.
</P>
<P>
African Conferences and Exhibitions Ltd. organizers chairman
Robin Wiseman told a press conference here today that papers
selected with the help of conference liaison committee
established with the assistance of the department of water
development would cover river basin management, water supply,
quality, conservation, economics and pollution control.
</P>
<P>
More than 110 companies will be exhibiting equipment and
services for water and environment protection.
</P>
<P>
The U.S., British, Belgian, French, Dutch, Danish and Middle
East companies will be showing their exhibits. In the showcase
will be some of the very latest water technology and techniques;
companies will display their equipment and services including
pipes, pumps, tanks, valves and wastewater treatment, irrigation,
drainage, monitoring and instrumentation, well-drilling
equipment, consulting and training. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
