<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tajik President Meets Opposition Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Tajik President Emomali
Rakhmonov and United Tajik Opposition (UTO) leader A. Nuri reached
agreement here today the implementation of a general agreement on
peace and national reconciliation in their country.
</P>
<P>
At a joint news conference, Rakhmonov and Nuri promised to
make joint efforts in opposing the armed forces that are blocking
the achievement of peace in the country.
</P>
<P>
Rakhmonov, who said he would work with Nuri, said that they
share the same aim of reviving Tajikistan, achieving peace and
stability and improving the people's living standards.
</P>
<P>
Nuri said all armed forces in Tajikistan should safeguard the
national interest and obey the leader of the National
Reconciliation Committee, otherwise they would lose the people's
support.
</P>
<P>
Since Tajikistan declared independence in September 1991, the
country has been plagued with a civil war. On June 27, 1997, the
government and the UTO signed the general agreement on peace and
national reconciliation.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the two sides completed the first round of
exchanging prisoners of war in July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
