<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices rose on the
Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index
gained 8.27 points to close at 1935.95 today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume stood at 170.33 million units, worth 335.32
million Singapore dollars (about 222.07 million U.S. dollars).
Advances overtook declines by 224 to 102, while 284 other counters
remained steady.
</P>
<P>
BBRC was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 11.12 million units. It was followed by Summit which
had 10.22 million shares traded. Rekapac was next with 9.78
million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose 60 cents to end at 33.2 Singapore dollars. The
Sembawang Corporation gained 40 cents to finish at 6.55 Singapore
dollars, while the Singapore Technology Aero closed 32 cents
higher at 4.12 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, The Thai Prime Fund was the biggest loser as
it declined 75 cents to finish at 6.25 U.S. dollars. Asean Fund
lost 40 cents to close at 11.7 U.S. dollars and the Overseas Union
Bank (OUB) Foreign fell 35 cents to end at 7.2 Singapore dollars.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
