<HEADLINE> Doohan Leads Local Riders in Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 12 (Xinhua) -- World champion Mick Doohan
won provisional pole position on Friday for the 500cc Catalunya
motorcycle Grand Prix in Montmelo, Spain on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Spaniard Carlos Checa delighted the home fans by pulling off
the second fastest time in the opening qualifying session at the
circuit near Barcelona despite crashing on a curve.
</P>
<P>
Another local rider Alex Criville was third fastest despite
still suffering the effects of a hand injury.
</P>
<P>
Doohan, who has already won the championship for the fourth
year in a row but who has never won the race, went round in one
minute 46.560 seconds on his Honda.  
</P>
