<HEADLINE> Dufaux Takes Yellow Jersey in Tour of Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland's Laurent Dufaux
took over as race leader in the Tour of Spain, winning the yellow
jersey after Friday's competition.
</P>
<P>
Overnight leader Laurent Jalabert of France cracked
dramatically on the Sierra Madre mountain to finish eight minutes
and 25 seconds behind the stage-winner, Frenchman Yvon Ledanois.
</P>
<P>
It meant that in 24 hours Jalabert, the 1995 winner, had
slipped from race favourite to also-ran.
</P>
<P>
Another big name, Spaniard Abraham Olano, quit the Tour after
racing only 83 of the 219.2 kilometers from Guadix. 
</P>
