<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak will meet
U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright Saturday in Alexandria,
a port city overlooking the Mediterranean Sea, Egypt's Middle East
News Agency (MENA) reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Their talks will deal with all issues relating to the Middle
East peace process, the agency quoted Egyptian Foreign Minister
Amr Moussa as saying. (Egypt-US-Albright)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- The third round of foreign secretary-level talks
between Pakistan and India will be held on September 15-18 in New
Dehli, a Foreign Office spokesman said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The last round of foreign secretary-level talks between the two
countries was held here in June. During the talks, the two sides
agreed to resolve their outstanding issues including the dispute
over Jammu and Kashmir. (Pakistan-India-Talks)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto reiterated
Friday his determination to carry out his pledged reforms.
</P>
<P>
"I will proceed with the reforms with an indomitable resolve,"
Hashimoto said during a press conference.
</P>
<P>
Hashimoto, who was re-elected for his second two-year term as
president of the ruling Liberal Democratic Party (LDP), named his
new cabinet Thursday.(Japan-Hashimoto-Reform)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- The Communist Party of China (CPC) opened its 15th
national congress at the Great Hall of the People here at 9:00
Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
When the session opened, all those present stood up to sing the
national anthem of the People's Republic of China. They also paid
a one-minute silence tribute to the late proletarian
revolutionaries and revolutionary martyrs, including Mao Zedong,
Zhou Enlai, Liu Shaoqi and Zhu De, and to the older generation of
proletarian revolutionaries who died not long ago, including Deng
Xiaoping, Chen Yun and Peng Zhen. (China-CPC Congress-Opening)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korea and Japan failed to narrow their
differences over rewriting a 1965 bilateral fisheries accord at a
two-day meeting here Thursday, local media said Friday.
</P>
<P>
During the fifth round of fishery talks this year, the two
sides put forward their respective proposals, according to Shin
Jung-seung, South Korea's chief delegate to the talks.
(S.Korea-Japan Talks)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos said here Thursday
his country wants to develop political and economic ties with
Russia and does not rule out cooperation in military technologies.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the ITAR-TASS news agency, Ramos said the
two nations' defense authorities are in "positive negotiations" on
military collaboration. (Russia-Philippines-Ties) 
</P>
