<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party Delegates Praise Jiang Zemin's Report (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Delegates to the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) shared
the view that the report given by Jiang Zemin at the opening
session has spoken the minds of the people, the army and the
Party as various delegations to the Congress began panel discussions
of the report this afternoon here.
</P>
<P>
Li Wenhai, president of the People's University of China and a
delegate from Beijing, said that Comrade Jiang Zemin's report has
a clear theme, is based on today's realities and gears to the
future, he said.
</P>
<P>
The CPC has been making painstaking efforts in exploring ways
to adapt Marxism to China's conditions, that is, to combine the
two, ever since the national liberation in 1949, the university
president stated. It is the requirement of both history and
reality to establish Deng Xiaoping Theory as the guiding ideology
of the Party, he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Zhiren, Party secretary of the Shandong Teachers
University, said Jiang's report was underlined by his call for
holding high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory. It is a
highly condensed statement that Deng Xiaoping Theory is Marxism of
present-day China, representing a new stage of development of
Marxism in China, he commented.
</P>
<P>
Doje Ridan, party secretary of Huangnan Autonomous Prefecture
of Tibetan Nationality in northwest China's Qinghai Province, said
the most splendid part in Jiang Zemin's report was the part "In
China today, it is Deng Xiaoping Theory, which integrates Marxism
with the practice of present-day China and the features of the
times, and this theory alone, that can settle the issues
concerning the future and destiny of socialism."
</P>
<P>
This conclusion, Doje Ridan said, is drawn from the experiences
of the CPC over the past few decades, including its setbacks.
</P>
<P>
Liu Rongchang, director of the Institute of Microbiology of the
Hebei Academy of Sciences, said an important aspect of Deng
Xiaoping Theory is to emancipate the mind and seek truth from the
facts.
</P>
<P>
Emancipating the mind means, among other things, breaking away
with the force of habit and assimilating new ideas, he said.
</P>
<P>
Gu Xiulian, Minister of Chemical Industry, said that Jiang's
report elevates the Party line adopted since the Third Plenary
Session of the 11th Central Committee to a new high. It has unique
features of the times and serves as a political declaration of
Party's third generation of leadership, she added.
</P>
<P>
The report broke through people's conventional ideas about the
forms of public ownership while upholding its dominant position,
the minister commented, adding it is of great significance.
</P>
</TEXT>
