<HEADLINE> PLA Delegates Say: Jiang's Report Inspiring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The report delivered by Jiang
Zemin at the opening session of the 15th National Congress of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) which opened here today is one that
inspires people to forge ahead, agreed delegates from Chinese
People's Liberation Army (PLA) in a panel discussion this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The delegates expressed their determination to work hard and
make concerted efforts to advance the cause of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics under the leadership of the CPC
Central Committee with Jiang at the core.
</P>
<P>
The delegates agreed that the report is a programmatic document
guiding the whole Party, whole army and people of all ethnic
groups of the country into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Holding high the banner of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics serves as the theme of the congress,
said Li Laizhu of the PLA delegation.
</P>
<P>
The issue of banner is a fundamental issue which has a vital
bearing on the fate of the Party and the country, he said, adding
that facts have shown that there is a great promise for the cause
of socialism so long as we hold high the great banner of the
Deng Xiaoping Theory in the new historical period.
</P>
<P>
Another PLA delegate Du Tiehuan believes that the realization
of the strategic goals set forth in Jiang's report
demands a close unity of the whole Party, the whole army and
people across the country and their joint efforts.
</P>
<P>
Du said that it is vital to consciously maintain the
authoritativeness of the CPC Central Committee with Jiang at the
core for this is the important guarantee for an all-round
advancedment of the cause of socialism with Chinese
characteristics into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Ding Wenchang and Tao Bojun agreed with Du, saying that the
army should at no time waver in subjecting themselves to the
absolute leadership of the Party Central Committee and the Central
Military Commission.
</P>
<P>
Army officers should be selected according to the primary
principle of combining both ethic integrity and political
awareness so as to guarantee that the gun will remain forever in
the hands of those who are loyal to the cause of the Party.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping's thinking on army building during the new
period is an important component of the Deng Xiaooping Theory, said
Shi Yunsheng.
</P>
<P>
Holding high the great banner of the Deng Xiaoping theory means
efforts should be made to implement his thinking on army building
and Jiang's exposition on army building, he added.
</P>
<P>
The delegates said they are determined to follow the decisions
of the Party Central Committee and the Central Military
Commission, and cut the armed forces by 500,000 within the coming
three years.
</P>
<P>
Attention should be paid to building the army through science
and technology, and improving the army's fighting capability to
win local wars under modern technology, especially under
high-technology, and taking the road of fewer but better troops
with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Liu Huaqing, Zhang Zhen, Zhang Wannian abd Chi Haotian, vice
chairmen of the Central Military Commission, attended the panel
discussion.  
</P>
</TEXT>
