<HEADLINE> China in Festive Mood as Congress Opens  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- A festival atmosphere has
pervaded the Chinese nation with today's opening of the 15th
Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) in Beijing, a
week-long meeting designed to set the country's development course
for the next century.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin's opening speech drew bursts of applause
from the crowd gathered at the Shougang Steel Complex in Beijing to
watch the live telecast of the opening event.
</P>
<P>
"I am now feeling at ease, after hearing Jiang's report," said
Xie Yuhuan, an employee of the steel company. He said he believes
that the Party Central Committee with Jiang at the core will
continue to hold high Deng Xiaoping's great banner of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
"The Party has become more and more mature," said Li Dongzhi, a
worker at the First Party Congress Site Memorial Hall in Shanghai,
where late Chairman Mao Zedong and 12 of his comrades founded the
Party in 1921.
</P>
<P>
According to Li, just 13 delegates represented the total of 53
Party members when the First Party Congress was held. Now more
than 2,000 delegates are attending the 15th congress, representing
58 million Party members.
</P>
<P>
Today's opening of the congress kept local farmers at home in
Yan'an, in northwest China's Shaanxi Province, where CPC was
headquartered from the late 1930s to the mid-1940s. "After hearing
Comrade Jiang's report, we feel that we will have an even better
future," said Hao Guiren, a local village Party head.
</P>
<P>
According to Hao, local farmers now live in newly-built
cave-houses, have bought large-screen Television sets and
installed direct-dial telephones.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, In Shenzhen, the first special economic zone and a
pilot city for the country's reform, local people said that the
opening of the congress has built up their confidence in the
current reform and opening drive.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
