<HEADLINE> 207 Kilograms of Heroin Seized in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Turkish police seized a total
of 207 kilograms of heroin in two operations in eastern and
southern Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency said
today.
</P>
<P>
Police raided a house in a village in eastern province of
Van, seizing 32 kilograms of pure heroin.
</P>
<P>
Another 175 kilograms of heroin were seized in an operation in
the Mediterranean province of Mersin.
</P>
<P>
Five people were arrested in the two anti-narcotics raids,
police officials were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, the agency failed to report when the raids were
carried out.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has long been known as an important route for
trafficking drugs into the European markets from Asia.
</P>
<P>
However, the volume of the drugs seized by police dropped
significantly because of a change in the smuggling routes in
Turkey, police said. 
</P>
