<HEADLINE> French Judge Issues Permit for Burying Diana's Chauffeur </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 12 (Xinhua) -- A French judge today issued the
permit for burying the body of Henri Paul, the chauffeur of
Princess Diana, after having made three toxicological examinations
on it.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse quoted the spokesman of the Paul family,
Dominique Melo, as saying that the judge in charge of
investigating the traffic accident which killed Diana had allowed
until 17:00 o'clock today the Paul family to present a new request
for examining the body of Paul.
</P>
<P>
The Paul family did not ask for a new examination after a third
examination of Paul's bloodstream confirmed two previous exam
results that the alcohol containment rate in his blood was at
least three times higher than the legal limit when the accident
took place.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, investigators had found elements of anti-depression
drug and calming drug in his blood.
</P>
<P>
The date for the funeral of Paul has not been announced by his
family. 
</P>
