elections will take place on October 12 this year, said a
presidential decree signed here today.
</P>
<P>
The campaign for the forthcoming presidential elections should
be started on September 27 and end on October 11, according to
the country's electoral law.
</P>
<P>
The result of the elections is expected to be declared on
October 27 this year.
</P>
<P>
The forthcoming presidential elections will be the second of
its kind in Cameroun after 1992.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, section presidents of the ruling Cameroun People's
Democratic Movement Party (CPDM) has called on Cameorunian
President Paul Biya to present his candidature in the forthcoming
presidential elections.
</P>
<P>
The call is contained in a motion of support presented today
in Yaounde at the end of a one-day seminar grouping the CPDM
section presidents from across the country.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this week, one of the major opposition political
parties, the National Union for Democracy and Progress of
Cameroun (NUDP), announced that it would not put out a candidate
in the forthcoming presidential elections.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the three major opposition political parties in the
country: the Social Democratic Front (SDF), the NUDP and the
Camerounian Democratic Union (CDU) have resolved to boycott the
forthcoming presidential elections.
</P>
<P>
The decision was announced in a joint declaration signed by
the three opposition parties at a press conference held in
Yaounde this evening.  
