<HEADLINE> Sugiyama Beats Po in Sony-Life Cup Women's Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Ai Sugiyama beat Kimberly Po of
the United States Saturday as Japan took the lead in the Sony-Life
Cup women's tennis tournament in Kobe, Japan.
</P>
<P>
Sugiyama, Japan's top player and No. 34 in the world, beat Po
6-1, 6-0 in 45 minutes.
</P>
<P>
In afternoon doubles play, Japan's Naoko Kijimuta and Rika
Hiraki defeated the American pair Jennifer Capriati and Lori
McNeil 6-2, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
The three-day exhibition event pits a team from the United
States against a team from Japan in five singles and two doubles
games. The winning team will receive dlrs 250,000.
</P>
<P>
Sunday, the last day of the competition, will feature one
doubles and three singles matches, including a battle between
Sugiyama and the world's No. 3 player Monica Seles.
</P>
<P>
Seles easily defeated Japan's Naoko Sawamatsu in the opening
match Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
