<HEADLINE> Investment, Trade Talks Successfully Concluded in Xiamen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The six-day '97 China
Investment and Trade Talks closed on a high note in Xiamen,
east China's Fujian Province, today.
</P>
<P>
As many as 1,668 contracts were signed during the talks,
involving a contractual foreign investment of about 6.2 billion US
dollars, announced Ma Xiuhong, director of the Foreign Investment
Department of the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation (MOFTEC), at a press conference today.
</P>
<P>
The flow of the foreign investment is directed toward the
fields of industries, communications, and energy, which account for
83 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Among them, 2.3 billion US dollars of foreign investment goes to
the industrial sector; 650 million US dollars to infrastructure
construction; 400 million US dollars to agriculture, 700 million
to the real estate; and 540 million to other sectors.
</P>
<P>
Two-thirds of the foreign investment comes from the Hong Kong,
Macao and Taiwan regions, and the per project average investment
scale reached 2.75 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The talks attracted 6,200 foreign and overseas Chinese
businessmen, with 2,200 from Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The central and western parts of the country have become the
new focus of foreign investment. Delegations from the two regions
have signed contracts for 495 projects, with a total funding of
3.1 billion US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
