<HEADLINE> Servicemen, Police Hail Opening of Congress, CPC Leadership (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The opening of the 15th
National Congress of Communist Party of China (CPC) on Friday
brought enthusiastic and favorable response from the rank and file
of the People's Liberation Army (PLA) and the People's Armed
Police (PAP).
</P>
<P>
All PLA and PAP officers and men, whether in their barracks,
patroling the borders, or involved in outdoor training, watched
with close attention live telecast of the opening of the Party
Congress Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
After hearing the work report delivered by Comrade Jiang Zemin,
many PLA and PAP officers and men expressed their firm desire to
closely unite around the CPC Central Committee with Jiang at the
core and to continue upholding the great banner of Deng Xiaoping
Theory.
</P>
<P>
The building of the armed forces must be reinforced so as to
safeguard the national security and the current modernization
drive, they pledged.
</P>
<P>
Policemen stationed in the former residence of late Chairman
Mao Zedong in the city of Shaoshan in Central-south China's Hunan
Province, armymen of the Chengdu Military Area Command in the
hometown of Deng Xiaoping in southwest China's Sichuan Province,
and officers and men of the 12th Company of a regiment of the PLA
Beijing Garrison patroling the Chang'an Avenue shared the same
following views:
</P>
<P>
"Comrade Jiang's report, taking Marxism, Mao Zedong Thought and
Deng Xiaoping Theory as the guidance, has confirmed the principal
guidelines of the Party in the primary stage of socialism and set
forth the great goal to realize the all-round national
rejuvenation and the complete reunification of the motherland, and
it has reflected the common aspiration of the whole Party, the
whole Army, and the people throughout China."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
