<HEADLINE> Servicemen, Police Hail Opening of Congress, CPC Leadership (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Moreover, troops stationed in special economic zones, namely
Hainan province, and the coastal cities of Shenzhen, Zhuhai,
Shantou and Xiamen in south and east China, discussed Comrade
Jiang's report, held that without the CPC and Mao Zedong Thought,
there would never have been a socialist New China. While without
Deng Xiaoping Theory, the country's present-day prosperity would
have been impossible.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, all headquarters in the central level and in major
command areas celebrated the opening of the Party Congress in
varied ways.
</P>
<P>
Many high-ranking PLA and PAP officers regarded Jiang's report
as a great guiding document as it provides a complete, in-depth
and scientific definition of the Party's most important theories,
guidelines and policies.
</P>
<P>
"The report has put forward new and still higher requirements
for the building of the defense sector and the Army, and it has
made a significant strategic decision to step up the improvement
of quality of the Army," they were unanimous in this view.
</P>
<P>
The officers pledged that all the armed forces will hold high
the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory, adhere to the principle
of the Party's absolute leadership over the Army, and rally still
more closely round the Party Central Committee and the Central
Military Commission, both with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, they pledged to abide by and absolutely accept the
command and leadership of the Party Central Committtee and the
Central Military Commission. 
