<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hot Topics Among Delegates to Party Congress (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Holding high the great banner
of Deng Xiaoping Theory has been the topic highlighting all panel
discussions of delegates to the on-going 15th National Congress of
the Communist Party of China here over the past few days.
</P>
<P>
The delegates hold that it is timely to stress the issue of
banner at the turn of the century. Holding high the great banner
of Deng Xiaoping Theory is the fundamental guarantee for China's
reform and opening up.
</P>
<P>
Wang Tianxi, deputy secretary of the Yunnan Provincial Party
Committee, said a country with 56 ethnic groups and a population
of 1.2 billion must have a banner which can unite the people,
chart direction and blaze a new trail on its way to the 21st
century. And this is Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
Wu Yi, minister of foreign trade and economic cooperation, said
the theme and the soul of the current congress is to hold high the
great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory. The CPC has long been
attaching great importance to the guidance of theory.
</P>
<P>
In the past, she said, "we rely on Mao Zedong Thought to
overthrow imperialism, feudalism and bureaucrat-capitalism to
build a new China. Today we rely on Deng Xiaoping Theory to carry
out reform and open to the outside world, which has helped to
improve the productive forces of China, raise the overall strength
of the national economy and improve the people's living standards.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's report has made breakthroughs in many areas of
theoretical research, indicating that the Communist Party is
mature, she added.
</P>
<P>
Zeng Peiyan, vice-minister of the State Planning Commission,
said the report was characterized by the following three features:
establishing the Deng Xiaoping Theory into the Party Constitution;
summerizing work in all trades theoretically and urging the people
to emancipate the mind.
</P>
<P>
The achievements made since China's reform and opening up in
the late 1970s have proved that the principle of taking economic
development as the central task of China set forth by Deng
Xiaoping was correct, he added.
</P>
<P>
Xu Kuangdi, a delegate from Shanghai, China's largest
industrial center, said Deng Xiaoping Theory is a beacon lighting
China to build socialism with Chinese characteristics and carry it
on to the next century. It is a major contribution to the
international communist movement.
</P>
<P>
Many delegates are in favor of the proposal of the Central
Committee to place Deng Xiaoping Theory into the Party
Constitution as its guiding ideology.
</P>
<P>
Chen Huanyou, Party committee secretary of Jiangsu Province,
said the report has been imbued with the spirit of emancipating
the mind and seeking truth from facts, answered a great number of
issues in China's reform and worked out programs for cross-century
development in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
