<HEADLINE> FM: Iran Gives Priority to Ties with Neighbors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Iran's foreign policy has
given priority to relations with neighboring countries and the
Persian Gulf littoral states, Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi said
here today.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with his Qatari counterpart Sheikh Hamad Ben
Jassem Ben Jaber al-Thani, Kharrazi said Iran will build mutual
confidence and create a friedly climate with the neighboring
countries, adding that "it is necessary to expand cooperation and
solidarity."
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi said that the Gulf plays a vital role in meeting the
world's energy needs, noting that Iran, as a Gulf littoral country
which has the largest coastal areas, plays an important role in
this strategic region.
</P>
<P>
"To regulate relations on a realistic basis, attention should
be paid to the role Iran can play in establishing peace and
tranquility in the region," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian foreign minister said that Muslim states should
have close relations in order to safeguard their people's
interests under current circumstances.
</P>
<P>
The Qatari foreign minister, who arrived here last night,
stressed that his country regards Iran as a powerful friend in the
region and wants to expand and strengthen relations with it.
</P>
<P>
He said that furthering relations between the two countries is
a step toward a more secure region and will be beneficial to all
regional countries.
</P>
<P>
"Qatar believes in having strong relations with Iran and wants
to expand mutual ties in political, economic and commercial
areas," he said.
</P>
<P>
He was to deliver a massage from Qatari Emir Sheikh Hamad Ben
Khalifa al-Thani to Iranian President Mohammad Khatami. No detail
of the message is available.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival at Tehran's Mehrabad Airport, he said that
Qatar's ties with its neighbors, Iran in particular, are clear
and solid.
</P>
<P>
He said that in his meetings with Iranian officials he intends
to become familiar with Tehran's views and also discuss further
expansion of Tehran-Doha ties. 
