<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ownership Form and Democracy Should Accord With National Condition, Says Theorist (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Speaking of the political restructuring, Xing said, "the
socialist democracy in China should be achieved by means of
ruling the country by law."
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the National People's Congress and its
Standing Committee have formulated, under the leadership of the
CPC, a series of laws and regulations.
</P>
<P>
"However," he said, "the achievement of socialist democracy
hinges on whether or not everything is handled according to laws."
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin said in his report that the socialist country
should be ruled by law, and this deals with an important link in
developing the socialist democracy, an important link in political
restructuring, he said.
</P>
<P>
Stressing the importance of ruling the country by law requires
the practice that all are equal before the law, he said. "All the
activities of the Communist Party of China should proceed within
the scope of the Constitution and laws of China," he said.
</P>
<P>
"China will draw on the good experience of the Western
democracy but will not copy the Western democracy, such as the
two-chamber system and multi-party electoral race," he stressed.
adding that every country has its own national conditions.
</P>
<P>
The socialist democracy in China has developed through a long
period of time. The Chinese Communist Party has accumulated rich
experience in establishing and improving the political
consultative system of multi-party cooperation under the
leadership of the CPC, he said.
</P>
<P>
The democracy is progressing in China. To date, the direct
election at village and township levels is spreading in the
country, winning praise from abroad, he said.
</P>
<P>
China's economy and culture were backward in the past and
people's education is not high. And the development of democracy
requires a process. With the gradual deepening of the country's
economic reform, socialist democracy in China will be further
improved, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
