<HEADLINE> Nearly 3,000 Persons Infected with HIV Virus in Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 3,000 people have been
tested HIV positive in Russia so far this year, the Itar-Tass news
agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The total number of HIV carriers in the country currently
stands at about 5,550. Among them 2,985 were tested positive with
the virus this year.
</P>
<P>
According to government reports, most of the people infected
the AIDS-causing virus by using contaminated syringes while taking
drugs.
</P>
<P>
Experts fear that at this rate, the number of HIV positive
people in Russia will reach 30,000 to 40,000 in just a matter of a
few years. 
</P>
