<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ownership Form and Democracy Should Accord With National Conditions, Says Theorist (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The emphasis of the economic
restructuring is to solve the understanding of the whole Party on
the form of ownership as pointed out in Jiang Zemin's report at
the opening session of the 15th National Party Congress, a
theorist said here today.
</P>
<P>
"On the basis of the improved understanding, the state will
make a strategic reorganization of existing state-owned
enterprises," said Xing Bensi, vice president of the Party School
of the Central Committee of Communist Party of China (CPC) and
editor-in-chief of "Seeking Truth", a theoretical magazine of te
CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
It is a "misunderstanding" to regard the readjustment and
improvement of ownership mentioned in Jiang's report simply as a
question of shareholding system, he stressed in an exclusive
interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"The public ownership is not equal to the state ownership," he
pointed out, explaining that the public sector includes not only
the state sector but also collective sector, and the collective
sector is also the public sector, and the state- and
collectively-owned elements in the sector of mixed ownership also
belong to the public sector.
</P>
<P>
The definition about the public ownership is based on an
analysis of various elements and therefore it is a "scientific
conclusion," he said.
</P>
<P>
In the course of a strategic reorganization of existing
state-owned enterprises, he said, the state would firmly control
the trades which have a vital bearing on the national economy and
some especially important economic interests, such as
communications and transport, banking, finance and some major
natural resources, while letting the state- and collectively-owned
firms or the mixed ownership to manage those less important
trades.
</P>
<P>
"This strategic reorganization is of great significance," he
said, adding that "this is actually to put the limited state
financial strength in the sectors that have a vital bearing on the
national economy. This seems that the investment line is short,
but actually it is an advance, not retrogression, and it is to let
the large enterprises which weigh heavily with the national
economy really develop."
</P>
<P>
Xing Bensi pointed out that reports saying that China will
sell off most of the state enterprises and only keep the small
number of large enterprises are "groundless." "It is impossible
for China to do so, and such a method will not work and only
leads to chaos," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The report has raised the development of diversed
forms of ownerships with the public ownership in the dominant
position to a height of a basic socialist economic system.
</P>
<P>
Xing said that the reason why the Chinese Communist Party has
set forth this development policy is because China's productive
forces are still low and the mono-public ownership would be unable
to promote the development of productive forces, and what is more,
it will may undermine their development.
</P>
<P>
The aim of allowing and encouraging a diversified form of
materializing the public ownership is to find a form of public
ownership which can help develop the productive forces to the
greatest possible extent, he said.
</P>
<P>
Xing said: "Practice has proved that it is wrong to think
that 'greater scale the public ownership, the better.' It
requires very earnest efforts to push up our economy and there
is not any short-cut."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970913.0095 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Investigators in Charge of Diana's Case Focus on Car </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Police Investigating the auto
accident which resulted in the death of Diana, Princess of Wales,
are examining the wreckage of the Mercedes S-280 sedan in which
she and three others were traveling.
</P>
<P>
Police have not excluded the possibility of a collision between
the car and another vehicle at the entry of the Alma tunnel.
</P>
<P>
The car will be completely "boned" and studied piece by piece
in a special police workshop, the Agence France-Presse (AFP)
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Investigators want to know the origin of a suspicious "scratch"
on the surface of the car, said AFP.
</P>
<P>
Police have found debris from a red rear auto light near the
shattered debris of headlights apparently from the Mercedes S-280,
the Paris-based daily Aujourd'hui said today.
</P>
<P>
All the vehicles and motorcycles of the photographers under
inquiry have been checked by police, but none of them showed any
indication of a clash with another vehicle, said the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The evening paper, France Soir, said police took a photo of the
Mercedes S-280 sedan with an automatic radar supervisor, while the
car was speeding past the Alma Bridge.
</P>
<P>
The photo, which caught the car registration number and clearly
showed Henri Paul, the chauffeur, at the wheel, was classified by
police, the paper quoted a leader of a police union as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, police denied having a picture of the car on its route
from the Hotel Ritz to the Alma underground tunnel where the fatal
crash occurred.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, a former lover of Henri Paul denied
today that the chauffeur from the Ritz Hotel was suffering from
depression or was a drunkard.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with le Figaro, Laurence P., who lived with
Paul from 1990 to 1995, said that Paul never took anti-depression
pills, nor drank alone.
</P>
<P>
But she said that the last time she contacted him was on the
phone in July 1996.
</P>
<P>
The London-based Daily Mirror said today that Paul took to
drinking after Laurence and another girl friend of his abandoned
him this summer.
</P>
<P>
"He drank until six o'clock in the morning in a bar near his
home," Vincent Martin, a taxi driver who knew Paul, told the paper.
</P>
<P>
A third toxicological test of Paul's body confirmed two
previous test results that he had imbibed three times as much as
the legally allowed volume of alcohol on the day the accident took
place.
</P>
<P>
A French judge issued a permit Friday for the burial of Paul's
body. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970913.0096 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hainan Maintains Stable Public Security Order (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The island province of Hainan
in south China, the country's largest special economic zone, has
maintained stable public order in recent years -- a great
improvement from its previous record.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, the number of its criminal cases has
been on a steady decline from 1990 to 1993, and the ratio has been
kept within eight crimes per every 10,000 residents in the past
three years.
</P>
<P>
The number of criminal cases registered in the first half of
this year has dropped by 27.9 percent over the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Hainan province was designated a special economic zone by the
central government in 1988, which drew in 100,000 people from all
parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
The frequent flow of people and assets have contributed to the
worsening of the public security, which hit an all-time low in
1989, when the number of criminal cases reached 9,000, nearly
double the number before the province was established.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has intensified its fight against
crime by setting up responsibility systems at all government
levels. Meanwhile, it also has increased financial input into the
public security organs.
</P>
<P>
During the Eighth Five-Year Plan (1990-1995) period alone, the
provincial government allocated more than 79 million yuan (9.5
million US dollars) to streamline the public security apparatus.
</P>
<P>
In-depth studies have been conducted by the public security
organs since 1992 to determine the key problems and areas. The
provincial capital, Haikou, were regarded as a hot-bed of criminal
activity where more than 40 percent of the crimes occurred.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970913.0097 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
