<HEADLINE> Romanian President Returns After China Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu returned to Bucharest this afternoon after a
five-day state visit to China, which he defined as "a complete
success."
</P>
<P>
The visit has yielded satisfactory results, the travel-worn and
weary president told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The visit to China shows that only through labor and honesty
can a country achieve progress and development, which is a feature
of modern China, Constantinescu said.
</P>
<P>
China has not only a glorious history but also a bright future,
Constantinescu said.
</P>
<P>
Sino-Romanian relations are characterized by mutual trust and
consultation, which will continue to be the principle for the
future development of relations between the two countries, the
president said.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu added that he had a sincere and frank talk with
Chinese President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Romania finalized its diplomatic strategy for the present and
for the 21st century as a result of his visit to China,
Constantinescu said.
</P>
<P>
While the integration into the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO) and the European Union remains a focal point
in the Romanian foreign policy, Romania will strive to further
develop ties with the Asian-Pacific region, especially with China,
the president said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
