<HEADLINE> Italy Blames Israel for Middle East Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister
Lamberto Dini said today that Israel's unilateral action which
runs against the peace accords caused the stagnation in the Middle
East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Dini said in an interview published today that both Israel and
the Palestine Autonomous Authorities are responsible for the
crisis in the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Terrorist activities should be stopped, but this is not the
only problem, he said.
</P>
<P>
Dini said that certain forces in the region have been trying to
deter the peace process, arousing anger and disappointments.
</P>
<P>
He said that terrorist acts and stalled peace talks were the
fruits of Israel's unilateral action which runs against the peace
accord and leads to revolts.
</P>
<P>
The way of the revolts should be condemned, but it is the
resistance by the Palestinians against the establishment of Jewish
settlements and other similar activities by Israel, Dini said.
</P>
<P>
He said that new proposals are needed to promote the peace
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
U.S. State Secretary Madeleine Albright has taken an unbiased
position in her current visit to the Middle East, Dini said.
