<HEADLINE> Team SCAR Takes Lead in Mild Seven Outdoor Quest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XICHANG, Sichuan Province, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The hard
charging team SCAR overtook Eco-Internet to lead the Mild Seven
Outdoor Quest after winning Saturday's race in Xichang, China's
Sichuan province.
</P>
<P>
The day's action began with a grueling 50-kilometer mountain
bike leg to the summit of Mor Pang Mountain. Teams then left their
bikes behind at the top and ran 20 kilometers back down the
mountain.
</P>
<P>
SCAR topped the standings with an overall time of 15 hours
14 minutes and 21 seconds. Eco-Internet was second in 15:19:38
and Red Bull third in 15:45:58.
</P>
<P>
The Mild Seven Outdoor Quest is a four-day adventure race being
held in Sichuan province, southwest China. Four-person teams are
contesting a variety of outdoor endurance sports from trail
running to offroad inline skating.
</P>
<P>
The winner after 250 brutal kilometers of racing will receive
the lion's share of 100,000 U.S. dollars. 
</P>
