<HEADLINE> India Wins South Asian Soccer Federation Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 13 (Xinhua) -- India won the first South
Asian Football Federation (SAFF) Championship by whipping the
Maldives 5-1 here Saturday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Nine minutes into the first half, a Maldivian defender made an
error, offering Jo Paul a chance to shot it into the net.
</P>
<P>
Six minutes later, India netted the second goal. Then in a
bully at the 19th minute, I.M. Vijayan scored a third goal for the
Indian team.
</P>
<P>
The Maldivians scored a goal two minutes before the break.
</P>
<P>
Soon after the second half kicked off, the Indians turned the
game into the shooting spree. At the 49th minute, Amit Das found
the target, and four minutes later, I.M. Vijayan repeated the feat
again to seal the big victory.
</P>
<P>
In another game for the third place, Pakistan beat Sri Lanka
1-0.
</P>
<P>
Nepal and Bangladesh were eliminated in the early games.
</P>
<P>
Crown Price Dipendra of Nepal gave the prizes to the winners. India
got a purse of 50,000 U.S. dollars, the Maldives 25,000 dollars,
Pakistan 15,000 dollars and Sri Lanka 10,000 dollars.
</P>
<P>
The nine-day SAFF tournament was jointly organized by the SAFF
and All Nepal Football Association and was sponsored by the Asian
Football Confederation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
