<HEADLINE> S. Leone Junta Sets up New Cabinet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Despite international demand
for immediate hand-over, the coupists in Sierra Leone who seized
power in May established Friday a 19-member cabinet to carry out
the junta's four-year transition program.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement faxed from the headquarters of the
West African Peace-keeping Force (Ecomog) in Monrovia, Liberia,
Major Johnny Koroma remains Chairman of the Armed Forces
Revolutionary Council (AFRC), Head of State, Commander in Chief
of the Armed Forces and Secretary of Defense.
</P>
<P>
Corporal Foday Sankoh, leaders of the ex-rebel group
Revolutionary United Front now believed held in Nigeria, was
appointed Vice-Chairman of AFRC, Deputy Head of State and Deputy
Commander in Chief of the Armed Forces.
</P>
<P>
Captain Saj Musa was named Secretary of Mineral Resources and
Chief Secretary, Ajibola Manly-Spain, Secretary of Foreign
Affairs, Osho Williams, Secretary of Transport and
Communications, and Colonel Collins Eldred, Secretary of Trade,
Industry and State Enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Among the new ministers designated as secretaries of state are
Brigadier m. l. Lymon (rtd) (Internal Affairs), Victor Brandon
(Development and Economic Planning), Joe Bangali (Finance) and
Umaru Deen Sesay (Youth, Sports and Social Mobilization).
</P>
<P>
Also named were heads of five directorates, three regional
secretaries, three presidential liaison officers (plos) and 37
advisers to the plos, including a representative each for Sierra
Leone labor congress, bar association, medical association,
students, chambers of commerce, journalists, teachers, petty
traders, women's union and civil defense units.
</P>
<P>
The junta also named 12 ambassadorial designates and 13 under
secretaries. 
