<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kiya's Double Helps Iran Beat China 4-2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, Northeast China, September 13 (Xinhua) -- A second-half
double from Mehdi Mahdavi Kiya inspired Iran to a come-from-behind 4-2
victory over China in the Group A match in the second round of the
World Cup Asian soccer qualifying competition here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
China led the first half 1-0 through defender Fan Zhiyi, who
converted a penalty kick after Zhang Enhua was fouled in the area
two minute before the break.
</P>
<P>
The hosts made it 2-0 nine minutes into the second half, when
full-back Sun Jihai beat the Iranian defence with a fine run down the
left and then passed the ball to Li Ming to slot home with a
spectacular volley.
</P>
<P>
The visitors then came back strongly by grabbing their first two
goals in a span of only seven minutes.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Karim Bagheri, who is with Arminia Bielefeld in the
German Bundesliga, capitalised a penalty for Iran after Fan fouled on
world's top international scorer Ali Daei in the 60th minute.
</P>
<P>
Iran then levelled the score in the 67th minute, when Kiya dribbled
the ball down the right and shot home calmly in a small angle.
</P>
<P>
Kiya, 20, then blasted home a sudden long-distance ball in the
84rd minutes to put Iran ahead.
</P>
<P>
The Iranians sealed their away victory through Aliaskhar Modir
Rousta, who hit the goal with four minutes remaining.
</P>
<P>
"We came here expecting to win by three goals," said Iranian
national coach Mohammad Mayeli Kohan after the game.
</P>
<P>
"China played quite well but we had more chances in the second
half," he added.
</P>
<P>
Kohan said the Iranian eleven made rapid improvement since last
year's Asian Cup, where they finished third, and Saturday's results
proved this.
</P>
<P>
Chinese coach Qi Wusheng said: "It was all too heartbreaking that
we squandered the 2-0 lead to lose. We played the second half poorly."
</P>
<P>
He said, "We appeared to lose our tactical direction after leading
by two goals. Our players need to hone their skills. They should
better both their personal technics and psychological strength."
</P>
<P>
The two teams will clash again in Tehran on October 17, when Iran
plays as the host. 
</P>
</TEXT>
