<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French President to Visit Principality of Andorra </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 13 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
will visit the Principality of Andorra, a valley state stuck
between France and Spain, next Monday and Tuesday, announced the
Elysee presidential palace today.
</P>
<P>
The French president is the inheritor of the co-princeship of
Andorra from the former kings of France, and exercises his power
as chief of state over Andorra together with the Bishop of Urgell
of Spain, Monseigneur Joan Marti Alanis, who is also co-prince of
the principality.
</P>
<P>
Chirac will meet with the chief of government Marc Forne Molne
and the General Syndic of the Andorran Valley, Francesc Arney,
holder of an officialdom coming down from the Medieval times.
</P>
<P>
The president will make a speech at the General Council of the
Valleys, the local parliament, on Tuesday and talk with people on
the Square of Poble of Andorra-the Valley to show his attachment
to the principality and its people, said the Elysee palace.
</P>
<P>
Chirac will also reassure the Andorrans that he and Monseigneur
Alanis are the guarantor of the continuity and independence of
Andorra.
</P>
<P>
Andorra has a population of 60,000 including 16,000 Andorrans,
30,000 Spanish, 4,000 French and 10,000 others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
