<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 4 Soldiers, 22 Separatists Killed in Senegal Clash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Four government soldiers and 22
separatists from the southern Casamance region of Senegal were
killed Friday in a clash in Santiaba-Mandjack near the frontier
between Senegal and Guinea-Bissau.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse quoted military sources of Senegal as
saying today that the clash took place when the government forces
were conducting a sweeping operation against the separatists
believed to be members of the Movement of Democratic Forces of
Casamance (MFDC), which has been fighting for independence since
1981.
</P>
<P>
MFDC gunmen Sunday attacked two villages near Senegal's border
with Gambia, killing five villagers. They also killed 12 civilians
during an attack upon a youth hostel Monday near the border of
Guinea-Bissau.
</P>
<P>
Senegalese President Abdou Diouf said that he is open to
dialogue, but ruled out signing a special statute for Casamance or
any concession in terms of territorial integrity of his nation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
