<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Delay in Euro Launch Dangerous to All, Says Chirac </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 13 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
said in the latest issue of the German weekly "Focus" that a delay
in the launching of the European single currency, the euro, will
be dangerous for all.
</P>
<P>
"There is a date and it should be respected. Otherwise we risk
burying the single currency," said Chirac in an interview with
"Focus" which was published today.
</P>
<P>
He said that a delay of euro will bring "very serious
consequences" to the market of exchange and the economy of many
countries, as well as "a deeper undermining than one can imagine"
of the European monetary union.
</P>
<P>
Chirac also stressed that the criteria set by the Maastricht
treaty for joining the euro should be respected, and that he
"shares exactly the same language" with German Chancellor Helmut
Kohl in respect of the date and criteria for the euro.
</P>
<P>
"The French government, formed from the former (left)
opposition, has decided to respect the criteria because this is in
the interests of France and Europe," said Chirac.
</P>
<P>
He added that the euro should be strong so that it can promote
growth and jobs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
