<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Communist Party Congratulates on CPC Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING September 13 (Xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the
Communist Party of Sri Lanka (CPSL) has sent a message of
congratulations to the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) on its 15th National Congress, which opened here
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The message said the CPSL conveyed fraternal wishes to the
CPC's 15th National Congress and wished the congress a complete
success.
</P>
<P>
Under the guidance of the theory of Comrade Deng Xiaoping, the
CPC has led China embarking on a road of economic modernization
and building socialism with Chinese characteristics, the message
said.
</P>
<P>
The CPC has not only brought tremendous material benefits to
the Chinese people, but also enriched the theory and practice of
the scientific socialism, the message noted.
</P>
<P>
The CPSL highly appreciated China's international activities
carried out under the leadership of the CPC. China has made
significant contribution to world peace and the establishment of a
new international political and economic order, said the message.
</P>
<P>
It added that the CPSL believed the 15th CPC National Congress
is an event of great significance, and that it would advance the
Chinese socialist cause to a new height. 
</P>
</TEXT>
