<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkish Military Urges Continuous Crackdown on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The powerful Turkish military
has reiterated that the government and the armed forces should
make joint efforts to combat the quickly expanding fundamentalism.
</P>
<P>
Local newspaper Turkish Daily News today quoted senior
military officials as saying that the Muslim fundamentalism still
constitutes a threat to Turkey's secularism and democracy.
</P>
<P>
These officials, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said that
the military will continue to support the current coalition
government in their fight against fundamentalists.
</P>
<P>
They also turned down the rumors that army generals have cast
doubt over the Mesut Yilmaz administration's determination to
fight fundamentalism.
</P>
<P>
The military had harshly criticized former Prime Minister
Necmettin Erbakan for his reluctance to take tough measures
against the extreme Islamists, but we don't have the same
complaint with the present government, a senior general told the
paper.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish media reported that the Turkish General Staff
regularly submits to the government reports on the country's
fundamentalism situation.
</P>
<P>
This shows that the Turkish armed forces are helping the the
government to fight the radical Islamists, and it is different
from the criticism of the former Erbakan government, newspapers
commented.
</P>
<P>
Military officials confirmed that the West Working Group,
organized by the General Staff to collect information on the
fundamentalism, will continue to cooperate with the government in
this respect.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish military, which calls itself a guarantor of
Turkey's secularism, played a leading role in forcing the June 19
stepping down of Turkey's first pro-Islamic Erbakan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
