<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin stressed on Friday the "vital
importance" "for restructuring state enterprises, which employ
more than 100 million people, at the opening of the 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
-- The 36,000 soldiers of the NATO Stabilization Force in
Bosnia have been put on alert as the country begins its municipal
elections this weekend. The United States has sent three planes to
jam the radio waves of radical Serb nationalists.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- French Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine Friday justified his
severe criticism of Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu,
saying that his point of view is widely shared by
others. Meanwhile, United States Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright said on Friday that she succeeded in persuading the
advisors of Netanyahu and Arafat to meet in one week in Washington.
</P>
<P>
