<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Diverse Forms of Public Ownership to Promote Economic Growth, Li Peng (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The affirmation that any
forms of public ownership should be used to serve socialism as
made by the on-going 15th National Congress of the Communist Party
of China will surely promote China's economic development, said Li
Peng here today.
</P>
<P>
Joining Beijing delegates in a panel discussion this morning,
Li Peng said the theme of the current Party congress is to hold
high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory for an all-round
advancement of the cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics to the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
He said the Party decided at its Seventh Congress to take Mao
Zedong Thought as its guiding ideology, which was a historic
decision with epoch-making importance. This contributed greatly to
the victory of the new democratic revolution, he said.
</P>
<P>
The 15th National Party Congress, he said, has decided to take
Deng Xiaoping Theory as its guiding ideology, which is another
historic decision with epoch-making importance.
</P>
<P>
The economic theory constitutes an important part in Deng
Xiaoping Theory and the ownership issue takes an important
position in the economic theory, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that the Chinese Communist Party made an important
decision to take economic development as the center of the Party's
basic line after the ten-year "Cultural Revolution." It is the
first great step in the emancipation of the mind, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the second great step in emancipating the minds of the
Chinese people is marked by the talks made by Deng Xiaoping during
his south China tour in 1992. The talks resulted in China's move
to establish a socialist market economy as a goal in economic
restructuring suggested by the 14th National Party Congress later
that year.
</P>
<P>
The decision made by the current Party congress which affirms
that public ownership takes diversified forms is another key step
in China's emancipation of the mind, Li said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
