<HEADLINE> Iranian Press Lashes out at Albright's Mideast Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Iranian press today lashed
out at the first visit to the Middle East by U.S. Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright since taking office in January.
</P>
<P>
The official English daily Tehran Times noted in its editorial
that Albright's on-going tour of the region "is obviously a visit
to work out a more effective anti-Iran policy with the Zionist
regime."
</P>
<P>
Another English daily Iran News said in its editorial that Iran
must arm itself to respond to U.S.-Israeli plots, which are aimed
at tarnishing Iran's image before the international public opinion.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper was apparently referring to Albright's remarks
made after meeting with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu
in Jerusalem earlier this week which termed Iran as a threat to
the regional peace and stability because it is seeking weapons of
mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
"In an orchestrated move, both Washington and Tel Aviv are now
out to launch a joint onslaught against what they see is
Iran-Russia growing relations," the Tehran Times said.
</P>
<P>
The Iran News criticized the United States for opposing other
countries maintaining normal ties with Iran and selling it nuclear
technology for civil and scientific purposes.
</P>
<P>
The paper accused Israel of refusing to sign the treaty of ban
on nuclear tests which Iran has already signed.
</P>
<P>
It stressed Iran does not seek weapons of mass destruction and
will prove that U.S. and Israel want to impose their hegemony over
Iran after making it vulnerable. 
</P>
</TEXT>
