<HEADLINE> China Lose to Iran in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, China, September 13 (Xinhua) -- China squandered a 2-0
lead to concede a 4-2 loss to Iran in a World Cup Asian zone
qualifier here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team opened scoring at the 43rd minute as captain
Fan Zhiyi converted a penalty shot to beat the Iranian
goal-keeper.
</P>
<P>
Nine minutes after interval, Li Ming made it 2-0 with a superb
right-foot shot.
</P>
<P>
It seemed the Chinese team would win their first match in the
Asian finals, but the Iranian team fought back steadily and
narrowed the gap to 2-1 also through a penalty kick.
</P>
<P>
Mehdi Mahdavi Kiya levelled the score 2-2 at the 67th minute
and went on to score his second goal in the match to give Iran a
3-2 lead 16 minutes later.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team appeared tired and their all-out attack left
too much space for the counter-attacks of the Iranians. A fatal
mistake made by the Chinese defence line at the 84th minute
enabled Ali Asghar Modir Rousta to seal the match 4-2 for the
Iranian team.
</P>
<P>
The defeat is a severe blow to the Chinese team in the
qualifying group which also includes Saudi Arabia, Kuwait and
Qatar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
