<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi on Significance of 15th Party Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The 15th National Congress of
the Communist Party of China, which is going on here at the turn
of the century, is a meeting of historic significance, Qiao Shi said
here today.
</P>
<P>
It will exert a great impact on China's development in the
21st century, he said in a panel discussion held here today by
delegates from east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
A number of delegates, including Li Zemin, shared the view that
Jiang Zemin's report, made at the opening session, summed up the
experience gained since China introduced the policy of reforms and
opening-up, concentrated the wisdom of the whole party and all the
people across the country. "It is a programmatic document
which inspires the whole nation in the march towards the new
century,' he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiao voiced his agreement to their opinion. He said facts had
shown that China would not have made the achievements today
without the guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory on building socialism
with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
This is the demand of the times and the aspirations of the
people, he added.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping put forward the statement that China is still in
the primary stage of socialism when preparations were underway
for the convention of the 13th National Party Congress, Qiao
recalled.
</P>
<P>
It is of vital importance that Jiang Zemin reiterated the
statement in his report to the opening session of the on-going
15th National Party congress. This shows that the Party has
improved its understanding on socialism and its national
condition, Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's report covered a wide range of key issues including
the experience gained in the reform of state-owned enterprises,
he noted.
</P>
<P>
China will become even more prosperous in the 21st century so
long as we combine theory with practice and work in a down-to-earth
attitude. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970913.0141 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Diverse Forms for Public Ownership to Promote Economic Growth, Li Peng (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China has made remarkable progress in economic development over
the recent few years. The reason for the great achievements, he
said, is that China has handled well the relations between reform,
development and stability and effectively curbed inflation.
</P>
<P>
With China's rapid economic development, he said, the
percentage of public ownership in the gross domestic product (GDP)
has dropped while that of non-public ownership has risen. As a
result, some state-owned enterprises are not operating so well,
which prompted doubts and arguments among some people.
</P>
<P>
However, Li Peng said, the latest statistics from the State
Statistics Bureau shows that in the mixed sector of the economy
the public ownership accounts for one third, or seven percentage
points of China's economy as a whole.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, he said, China produced 6.9 trillion yuan in the GDP,
of which public ownership accounted for 5.2 trillion, or 76
percent. This means that the public ownership still takes a
dominant position in China's economy.
</P>
<P>
On the impact of foreign investment on China's domestic
industries, Li said the move will not affect China's domestic
industries as long as the country sticks to the principle of
innovation and absorbing it after introducing technologies and
management expertise from abroad.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng said there exist great financial potentials both in the
international and domestic capital markets. In the domestic
market, he said, China's savings deposits have reached four
trillion yuan which can quench fund shortage in China's economic
construction.
</P>
<P>
Share-holding is an organizational form of capitals for modern
enterprises which can apply in both capitalist and socialist
countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
On the development of stock market, Li said China lacks
experience in standardizing stock market. Stock market is a source
of financing for construction and technological transformation for
enterprises and it can help promote management for share-holding
firms, he said.
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged that there had been chaos in China's stock
market but it returned to normal soon after the State Council took
effective measures.
</P>
<P>
He told the congress delegates that China will list more firms
in the stock market. Stock market, he said, should support the
reform of large state firms. The Chinese government encourages
those enterprises with advantages and good economic returns to
merger those debt-ridden enterprises so that they can complement
each other.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
