<HEADLINE> Vietnam Seizes Over 516 kg of Poor-Grade Uranium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam has seized 516.56
kilograms of poor-grade uranium since october 1993, Nguyen Tien
Nguyen, director of the Vietnam Atomic Energy Commission said
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The seized uranium was solid waste discharged from the process
of enriching uranium, said Nguyen Tien Nguyen.
</P>
<P>
None of the uranium seized in Vietnam so far had been of the
dangerous u238 type, said the director. 
</P>
