<HEADLINE> Danish Shuttlers Dominate Singles Finals at U.S. Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Danish shuttlers dominated
the men's and women's singles finals by taking three out of four
berths at the U.S. Open badminton tournament at Orange,
California, on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Olympic champion and second-seeded Poul-Erik Hoyer-Larsen
survived a tough semi-final game against Luo Yigang of China.
</P>
<P>
Hoyer-Larsen, the only seeded player to reach the semi-finals
in men's singles, lost the first set 16-17 but came back into the
game by taking the following two sets 15-11, 15-2.
</P>
<P>
Hoyer-Larsen's win made the men's singles final an all-Danish
final as Peter Gade-Christensen also entered the final with a
15-9, 15-8 victory over giant-killer jeroen van Dijk of the
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Denmark also booked a berth in the women's singles final
through top-seeded Camilla Martin who beat third-seeded Han Jingna
of China 11-3, 11-3 in the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Martin will take on another Chinese shuttler Dai Yun, the
second-seeded player, in the singles finals.
</P>
<P>
Dai Yun advanced after beating fourth-seed Marina Andrievskaya
of Sweden 11-7, 12-9.
</P>
<P>
China also got a berth each in the men's and women's doubles
finals through Zhang Wei and Liu Wong and Tang yongshu and Qin
Yiyuan respectively.
</P>
<P>
Zhang and Liu beat Victo Wibowo and Tony Gunawan of Indonesia
11-15, 15-11 and 15-10 while top-seeded Tang and Qin outplayed
third-seeded Danish pair of Majken Vange and Ann Jorgensen 15-8,
15-4.
</P>
<P>
The final of the mixed doubles will see a battle between Kim
Dong Moon and Ra Kyung Min of South Korea and third-seeds Bambang
Suprianto and Rosalina Riseu of Indonesia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
