<HEADLINE> Johnston Regains WBC Lightweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 12 (Xinhua) -- American Stevie Johnston
regained his World Boxing Council (WBC) lightweight title with a
unanimous decision over Saul Duran of Mexico in Las Vegas on
Friday night.
</P>
<P>
The judges scored the 12-round bout at Caesars Palace 117-111,
119-110 and 118-110 for Johnston, who improved his record to 23-0.
</P>
<P>
Johnston, who sustained a deep cut over his right eye in the
first round, fought the last three rounds with the eye swollen
shut.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Duran saw his record drop to 25-3. 
</P>
