<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 6 Lebanese Soldiers Killed in Israeli Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Six Lebanese soldiers were
killed and four others wounded Friday in an Israeli attack in
south Lebanon, local newspaper the Beirut's Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
At 23:10 (20:10 GMT) local time, several Israeli helicopters
fired missiles at a Lebanese army position between the three towns
of Arabsalim, Houmin Fawqa and Jarjoueh in the Iqlim Tufah region.
</P>
<P>
The position faces the Israeli-occupied border enclave in south
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
A Lebanese woman living nearby was also wounded in the fighting
and later died in hospital, the newspaper added.
</P>
<P>
Half an hour earlier, one Lebanese soldier was wounded in
another Israeli attack on a military school in Arabsalim.
</P>
<P>
The Lebanese army responded to the attacks with machine-gun
fires at the Israelis.
</P>
<P>
In another development some hours earlier, several fighters of
the Lebanese Islamic Hezbollah were killed and four Israeli
soldiers wounded in their clashes on the edge of the enclave.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian-backed resistance force announced in a communique
that it had ambushed an Israeli army patrol which was attempting
to infiltrate into the Lebanese-controlled areas.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese security sources said that the Hezbollah fighters
fired anti-tank rockets and automatic weapons at the patrol near
Jabal al Rafai, in the no-man's land between the Israeli-occupied
zone and the rest of south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The conflict in south Lebanon has intensified in recent weeks,
with Lebanese guerrillas foiling a Israeli commando raid last week
near the Lebanese port city of Saida, which left 12 Israeli
soldiers dead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
