of Afghanistan when Qezelabad village in the vicinity of the
Mazar-i-Sharif airport was seized by the union front fighting
against Taliban.
</P>
<P>
He described the killing as a "savage and anti-Islamic act" and
expressed concern over the escalation of war and bloodshed in
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
He called on the international organizations, including the
international Red Cross, to denounce such savage acts, as well as
the prevailing insecurity and violation of human rights in
Afghanistan. 
