<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Holds National Funeral for Mother Teresa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 13 (Xinhua)-- A national funeral was held
for world noted Nobel laureate Mother Teresa in Calcutta today.
</P>
<P>
Mother Teresa passed away at her home at the headquarters of
the Missionarie of Charity in Calcutta on September 5 due to a
cardiac arrest. She was born on August 26,1910 in Yugoslavia of
Albanian parents and came to India's Calcutta in 1928 when she was
18 years old. Since then she spent all her life working for the
poor people. In 1979 she was awarded Nobel Peace Prize.
</P>
<P>
Physically handicapped people, the poor and the beggars, lined
up along the route of the funeral procession to bid farewell to
her. Crowds threw flowers and wiped tears as the cortege passed
by.
</P>
<P>
The Archbishop of Calcutta, Henry DOS's in his speech spoke
highly of the Mother Trees. He said that the Mother's greatest
contribution to the world was that she saved the people the value
of dignity and love.
</P>
<P>
Indian President Kocheril Raman Narayanan, Prime Minister Inder
Kumar Gujral as well as some world leaders took part in the
funeral ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
