<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> b d p 1771 China-Congress-Army (Details Added) Liu Huaqing on Armed Forces Cut </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Liu Huaqing today described
the reduction of China's armed forces by 500,000 in the next three
years as a "major measure to improve the quality of the People's
Liberation Army (PLA)".
</P>
<P>
The reduction was announced by Jiang Zemin in his report to the
on-going 15th National Party Congress Friday morning. China
already cut its armed forces by one million in the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
Joining other army delegates to the congress in a panel
discussion, the Chinese military leader said China will work hard
to improve scientific research in national defense and improve the
overall quality of weaponry and equipment.
</P>
<P>
"It is an important part of Deng Xiaoping's thinking on army
building in the new period to improve the quality of the Chinese
army and take the road of fewer but better troops. This is a
correct choice to materize the modernization of armed forces in
China," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We should take the chance to readjust the system of and the
establishment for the army and make it smaller in size but more
capable in strength, he added.
</P>
<P>
It is imperative to train a large number of military personnel
who know the art of modern wars, especially commanders who are
well versed in high technology, through improved education at
military institutes and intensified training in the army units, he
said.
</P>
<P>
"We should adhere to taking the military thinking of Mao Zedong
and Deng Xiaoping's thinking on army building in the new period to
guide the foreseeing of the trend of global military development
in a scientific way, emancipate the mind, blaze new trails and
explore the military theory with the characteristics of the
Chinese army," Liu said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
