<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970913.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Diary of Party Congress Delegates (Sept. 13) - 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 13 (Xinhua) -- (At Xinhua's request, some
delegates to the ongoing 15th National Congress of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) write what they see, discuss and think during
the congress in diary form, which we think will provide outsiders
with some information about this major event. The following diary,
the second of its kind, was written by Lu Yongxiang, president of
the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS). -- editor)
</P>
<P>
In his report delivered at the opening session of the congress
yesterday morning, Jiang made a complete and incisive exposition
about the future and destiny of China. The report could well be
regarded as the Party's cross-century declaration.
</P>
<P>
Yet what encourages me most is the fact that science and
technology have been regarded as essential elements for achieving
economic progress. The report also focuses on the policy of
"invigorating China with science and technology" and the target to
improve the general quality of the entire people. I think that
education in science and technology has never received so much
attention in the past.
</P>
<P>
The report reflects the characteristics of the period and the
requirements of the socialist modernization drive. In addition,
the report shows that the collective Party leadership has a good
command and judgement over the development trend of the world.
</P>
<P>
The challenges China faces today mainly stem from increasingly
acute competition worldwide, as well as the pressure China feels
because it lags behind the developed countries in terms of economy
and science and technology.
</P>
<P>
The coming 21st century will be a period marked by economic
globalization, better-education and fast development of science
and technology. New scientific discoveries and technological
revolution will give rise to new industrial revolutions, which
will ultimately change the feature of the economic and social
life, and even the world.
</P>
<P>
Science and technology will be a key element in determining
economic development, as well as the fundamental index of the
comprehensive national strength.
</P>
<P>
The quality and creativity of the people, I believe, will be
the foundation and motivation to enhance the competitiveness of the
country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
