<DOCNO> XIE19970913.0178 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French ELF Oil Co. in Angola to Produce 100,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 13 (Xinhua) -- France's ELF Oil Company will
produce 100,000 barrels of oil daily in Angola by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Patrior Tuibart, general manager of the ELF Exploration
Angola, a branch company of ELF, made the statement to the press
the other day.
</P>
<P>
He said, the production will mainly come from sea-bed drilling
in Angola. And by 2005, the productions will reach 200,000
barrels.
</P>
<P>
It is predicted that ELF Oil Company will invest 1.5 to 2
billion U.S. Dollars in the Girassol oil field which was
discovered in April, 1996, to boost production. At present, the
daily production of the oil field is 2,800 barrels.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the Dalia No.1 oil field recently tapped in the
sea bed of Angola, the manager said, this is the biggest oil
field the company discovered in Angola, with a daily production of
16,000 barrels from the first well.
</P>
<P>
It is still early to estimate the reserve of the oil field, he
added, but admitting this is a major discovery of the company.
</P>
<P>
According to Tuibart, ELF company has been well acquainted
with the geological structure in Angola after spending many years
in the country. However, he added, it still requires more oil
fields to realize the goal of 100,000 barrels daily by 2000.
</P>
<P>
At the moment, the company is sending out Angolans to France,
Portugal and other European countries to study relevant
technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
