<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dimitry Sautin Wins Men's 3-meter Springboard Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Olympic champion Dimitry
Sautin of Russia earned 456.75 points for the title of the men's
3-meter springboard title at the World Cup diving here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Sautin faced a serious challenge from Zhou Yilin and Xu Hao of
China. But he still managed to win the title with an advantage of
less than one point.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Yilin took the silver medal at 455.79, followed by Xu Hao
in the third place at 451.53 points.
</P>
<P>
Xu and Zhou combined to win the men's 3-meter synchronized
diving title on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Sautin scored his highest score of 83.64 points in his fifth
dive. Zhou Yilin had his best dive in the third round when he
collected 90.30 points. But he could not maintain that high level
throughout the finals.
</P>
<P>
The women's 10-meter platform synchronized title was taken by
Chi Bin and Wang Rui of China. Their winning score is 312.54
points.
</P>
<P>
Anke Piper and Ute Wetzing of Germany took the silver medal at
a total of 268.47 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
