<HEADLINE> Albanian Prime Minister Wins Economic Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Prime Minister Fatos
Nano returned home today after his four-day visit to Luxembourg,
Austria and the headquarters of the European Union and NATO.
</P>
<P>
The local media reported that Nano won a total of 250 million
U.S. dollars in pledged funding from the EU, the European
Investment Bank and Luxembourg.
</P>
<P>
During the four-day visit, Nano said, his hosts expressed
satisfaction over the new Albanian government's efforts in
restoring social order and institutional reforms.
</P>
<P>
Nano, who was elected in the elections of June 29 and took
office on July 25, assured them that the new cabinet will not
repeat the previous government's mistakes and will establish what
he called democratic institutions in the country and practice an
open market economy.
</P>
<P>
During the tour, Nano also signed an agreement with NATO on an
Partnership for Peace program, which was seen as a sign of closer
relations with the transatlantic defense bloc. 
</P>
</TEXT>
