<DOCNO> XIE19970913.0221 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Investment and Trade Fair Opens in Xi'an </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 13 (Xinhua) -- China's Xi'an Investment and
Trade Forum, an annual event, opened Friday in Xi'an, capital of
the northwestern Shaanxi Province, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
More than 3,000 investors and business representatives from
at home and abroad attended the five-day event, which is
sponsored by local government of Xi'an City.
</P>
<P>
About 115 key projects are available at the ongoing forum for
investment and cooperation, covering infrastructure and tourism
facilities, agriculture and food-processing, machinery, and etc.
</P>
<P>
Apart from local enterprises and companies in Xi'an, those from
Beijing, Shanghai, Shandong and Gansu provinces and Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region are also seeking investment and cooperation for
their projects and products at the forum.
</P>
<P>
Xi'an, a city which is more than 3,000 years old, is the
largest city in Northwest China, and a well-known tourist attraction.
</P>
<P>
The investment and trade forum have been held every year since
1991. It has become the most important annual promotion to speed
up the city's development and opening-up to outside world. 
