<HEADLINE> Exports Surge in Subic, Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Export earnings of companies
based in Subic Bay, the northern Philippines, grew by 65 percent
to 349.7 million U.S. dollars in the first eight months of this
year, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Data released by the Subic Bay Management Authority showed that
in August alone, the exports revenue reached 35 million, 26
percent higher than a year ago.
</P>
<P>
The data attributed the increase in export earnings to the
rising number of locators in Subic, a special economic zone
converted from a former U.S. naval base.
</P>
<P>
There are 259 foreign and local companies, mostly
export-oriented firms, that have located their projectors in
Subic. Most of these firms are now operational.
</P>
<P>
The fourth informal leadership meeting of the Asia Pacific
Economic Cooperation (APEC) forum was held in Subic last November.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
