<HEADLINE> New UNIDO Director General Elected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Industrial
Development Organization (UNIDO) today elected Argentine economist
Carlos Alfredo Magarinos its new Director General.
</P>
<P>
Magarinos, 35, Argentine representative of trade and economy to
Washington, will replace Mauricio Maria Campos of Mexico as the
UNIDO Director General after his qualifications are approved by a
UNIDO plenary session in December.
</P>
<P>
The incumbent UNIDO director general will leave his post by the
end of November after four years of service.
</P>
<P>
The UNIDO, founded in 1967, is a multilateral technological aid
organization of the U.N. General Assembly. Its main task is to
promote and speed up the developing countries' industry.
</P>
<P>
The headquarters of the UNIDO is based in Vienna. 
</P>
</TEXT>
