<HEADLINE> Cuba Confiscates 500,000 Dollars Worth of Marine Species </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Cuban authorities have
confiscated over the past 12 months half a million dollars worth
of marine species such as lobster and shrimp, Juan Fung, director
of the Fishing Inspection National Office, reported today.
</P>
<P>
Besides the 66 tons of marine species confiscated, 70
kilometers of nets, 260 boats and more than 50 vehicles were also
seized.
</P>
<P>
More than 6,000 people have been penalized for violating
fishing regulations, and the fines imposed has surpassed a level
of 7 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Over recent months, illegal activities of fishing have been
checked to a great extent thanks to efforts made by the Fishing
Industry Ministry to promote legality, order, and discipline in
its sphere of influence, said Fung. 
</P>
