<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazilian Coffee Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian coffee bean
exports reached 1.84 million dollars in the first eight months of
this year, a 7 percent increase over the whole of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Sales abroad reached 9.79 million 60-kilogram bags, a 48
percent increase over the same period of 1996, said the Brazilian
Association of Coffee Exporters.
</P>
<P>
The price of a bag of coffee was 188.13 U.S. dollars in the
average.
</P>
<P>
The exporters association said the bigger income was due to an
increase in international quotations and to a bigger volume of
demand. The price of the product increased 98 percent in the past
12 months.
</P>
<P>
The association foresees that this year 16.5 million bags will
be exported, a 27 percent increase over 1996, and the income will
reach 3.1 billion dollars, an 80 percent increase. 
</P>
</TEXT>
