<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Farmland Reclamation Company Success In Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The first farmland
reclamation company in China's Guizhou province, which opened in
March in Luodian county, has succeeded in turning hillsides into
terraced fields by reclaiming nearly 32 ha of barren hillsides.
</P>
<P>
Huang Zugen, a farmer in the village of Xinyuan, bought 0.6 ha
of the improved land and said, "It really pays to buy 30-year
land-use rights at some 30,000 yuan per hectare."
</P>
<P>
The company needed to turn mountainous karst areas into
terraced land to improve farmers' lives and productive capacity,
explains Yu Xueqiang, the county's Party secretary.
</P>
<P>
The company uses four management personnel and more than 60
rural laborers for this effort and has great development potential
because the county has only 0.04 ha of farmland per capita.
</P>
<P>
The province has turned 262,000 ha of hillsides into farmland
since 1991, and needs to reclaim another 66,000 ha of wasteland to
meet farmers' needs.
</P>
<P>
The company has provided an example for the rest of the
province in opening up land in a particular, market-oriented way.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970913.0241 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Becomes Largest Bamboo Grower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 13 (Xinhua) -- China now has the world's
biggest bamboo industry, which brought in a total output value of
over 12 billion yuan in 1996, including 6.3 billion yuan from
processing and 400 million US dollars from exports.
</P>
<P>
The bamboo sector is among the country's four fledgling
forestry-related industries, along with the floral, forest tourism
and forest food products industries.
</P>
<P>
The statistics were issued at the ongoing First China Bamboo
Festival held in Ji'an County, in east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
China now leads in the world in terms of planting acreage,
species and varieties, output and bamboo in stock, according to
official sources.
</P>
<P>
At present, over 4.4 million ha. of bamboo are growing in the
country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
