<HEADLINE> Rusedski Reaches Top 10 in ATP Ranking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Greg Rusedski became the first
British player to reach the top 10 in ATP rankings after his
quarter-final victory over Lucas ARnold of Argentina at
Bournemouth on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Rusedski, runner-up in the U.S. Open, beat Arnold 7-6 (7-3),
6-3 to grarantee himself the berth within the top 10 of ATP
rankings.
</P>
<P>
Rusedskl will face top-seeded Carlos Moya of Spain in
Saturday's semi-finals. Moya advanced after beating Davide Scala
of Italy 6-3, 6-4 in the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
The ATP Tour confirmed on Friday that the Canadian-born
Rusedski will be No. 10 when the rankings come out next week.
</P>
