<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Meteorological Cooperation Between Two Sides of Taiwan Straits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The meteorological department
of Taiwan Province has expressed its interest in cooperating with
its mainland counterpart to study forecasting of thunderstorms,
according to reports of Taiwan newspapers.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan has suffered great economic loss in recent months as a
result of frequent heavy storms. Just prior to the storms, the
province's meteorological department received weather information
covering mainland China via Japan or the United States, but the
data was usually incomplete and late.
</P>
<P>
The source cloud of the thunderstorms hitting Taiwan is usually
formed above the mainland, and complete information on its
structure is needed to make a precise forecast for the coming of
the thunderstorms, said a professor with the Research Institute of
Meteorological Science under Taiwan University. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
