<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, Septemer 12 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Albert Costa and his
fellow Spaniard Alberto Berasategui both entered the semi-finals
of the Marbella Open tennis tournament on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Costa beat Andrea Gaudenzi of Italy on Friday while
second-seeded Berasategui rolled over Julian Alonso of Spain 6-1,
6-2.
</P>
<P>
Berasategui will take on Dominik Hrbaty of Slovakia in the
semi-finals. Hrbaty, the only non-spaniard player in the
semi-finals, beat Karim Alami of Morocco 6-3, 7-5 in the
quarter-finals on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The last semi-finalist of the tournament is Galo Blanco of
Spain who downed his compatriot Francisco Roig 7-6 (8-6), 6-3 on
Friday. 
