<HEADLINE> Maradona to Play on Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Diego Maradona said he
would play for Boca Juniors on Sunday and then receive a doping
test.
</P>
<P>
Maradona, who failed a doping test in August but denied he took
drugs, said that even if soccer authorities didn't pick his name
out of the hat, he would insist to receive a doping test.
</P>
<P>
A federal judge orgered the Argentine Football Association not
to ban Maradona until an investigation is completed.
</P>
<P>
Maradona trained with his teammates on Friday. On Sunday, Boca
plays Maradona's former team, Newell's Old Boys. 
