<HEADLINE> Cuba, United States Win in World Cup Volleyball Qualifying </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Cuba and the United States won
their first matches in both the men's and women's North and
Central American and Caribbean Volleyball Championships on Friday.
</P>
<P>
In the women's competitions, the American team beat Mexico
15-5, 15-3 and 15-4 while the Cuban women's squad downed Costa
Rica 15-3, 15-0 and 15-0 at Caguas, Puerto Rico, on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The North and Central American and Caribbean Volleyball
Championships serves as a qualifier for the World Cup to be held
this year in Japan.
</P>
<P>
The American men's spikers enjoyed an easy victory of 15-1,
15-5 and 15-1 over underdogs Barbados.
</P>
<P>
In the other matches played on Friday, the Cuban men's team
beat Dominican Republic 15-2, 15-5 and 15-7 while the Dominican
Republic women's team pulled up an upset victory of 15-11, 15-7,
12-15 and 15-12 over their Canadian rivals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
