<HEADLINE> Synchronized Diving Has Bright Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The International
Swimming Federation (FINA) said that synchronized diving had a
bright future and could make the Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
FINA director Cornel Marculescu said during the World Cup
diving tournament on Friday that the International Olympic
Committee (IOC) had asked FINA to include the synchronizing diving
in the world swimming championships, signaling the sport could get
an OK in the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The synchronizing diving will be included as a medal event in
the 1998 world championships in Perth, Australia, Marculescu
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
