<HEADLINE> Edmundo Sets Brazilian Record with Six Goals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Star striker Edmundo set a
Brazilian soccer championship record by netting six goals in the
same game in Rio de Janeiro on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Edmundo scored all goals in Vasco's 6-0 blanking of Uniao Sao
Joao. He came short of seven goals as he missed a penalty kick in
the 83rd minute.
</P>
<P>
Despite his scoring talents, Edmundo is unlikely to be on the
Brazilian team at next year's World Cup in France. His hot temper
led national team coach Mario Zagallo to recommend psychological
counseling for the one sometimes referred to as "The Animal."
</P>
</TEXT>
